<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-05-11T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-05-11T11:00:00-05:00" n="809" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d809">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/1544: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-05-11T17:00:00+01:00">May 11, 1939—5
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received May 11—11:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>663. Talked to MacDonald this morning. For parliamentary purposes it
                                would be advisable to postpone Palestine statement until Wednesday
                                instead of Monday. They are sending to Lindsay the complete text of
                                the White Paper and not just the outline, with instructions to show
                                you the whole thing.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kennedy</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>